        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 3:54PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 354 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northwest of Adena, or 15 miles southwest of Fort Morgan,
moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Morgan, Brush, Wiggins, Log Lane Village, Adena School,
Twelve-Mile Corner, Adena, Weldona, Hoyt, Goodrich, Jackson
Reservoir, Orchard and Hoyt Beet Dump.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
